# Go coverage profile — throwaway intermediate from `magus run coverage`. The
# rendered coverage.svg badge is committed; the profile is not.
coverage.out

# Local build artifacts: `go build ./cmd/<name>` at the repo root drops the bare
# basename here. /magus-* is a wildcard so a newly added cmd/magus-* tool is covered
# without editing this list (an explicit list once missed magus-spelldocs and swept
# the binary into a commit); the non-prefixed tools are named individually.
/magus
/magus-*
/coverage-badge
/langservice-manifest
/buzz-playground

# release output from `magus run release` — cross-compiled tarballs + SHA256SUMS,
# published to the GitHub release, never committed
/dist/

# macOS directory metadata
.DS_Store

# magus runtime cache
.magus/

# SCIP code-symbol indexes are build artifacts (magus writes them under .magus, but a
# manual `scip-*` run can drop one in the tree); never commit them.
*.scip

# compiled Go test binaries (go test -c / bench runs)
*.test
